INHERITANCE

It is a process of acquiring the properties(data + methods). Reusability is the main use of inheritance

The one which gives - parent class
The one which takes - child class

Inheritance can be achieved by using Extends keyword

Types of Inheritance:
1. Single A->B
2. Multiple A->B->C
3. Multilevel A+B->C (Not Supported, however can be fixed by Interface)
4. Hierarchial A->B, A->C, A->D

Access Modifiers
1. Default - when no access modifier is specified
2. public -from everywhere in the program
3. protected - within same package
4. private - only within the class